urious</span></div><div><span class=3D"text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-5=
00 font-bold block mb-1">Why it works</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-200/80=
">This script refuses the transactional sex trap while also refusing reject=
ion. It creates a bridge: you're saying yes to connection, just not the for=
m they offered. It signals that intimacy is possible, but only if you both =
show up emotionally first. This is the only way to rebuild the intimacy (40=
) without resentment.</p></div><div><span class=3D"text-[10px] uppercase te=
xt-emerald-500 font-bold block mb-1">Expected Response</span><p class=3D"te=
xt-emerald-200/80">Your partner may feel initially disappointed, but if you=
 follow through with genuine curiosity, they will often open up. This 15-mi=
nute conversation frequently leads to more authentic physical connection th=
an the original initiation would have.</p></div><div><span class=3D"text-[1=
0px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold block mb-1">If it fails</span><p =
class=3D"text-emerald-200/80 border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/10 rounded=
 p-2 text-red-200">If your partner says 'Never mind' or withdraws, say: 'I =
know that felt like rejection. It's not. I'm trying to do this differently =
so it feels good for both of us. Can we try again tomorrow when we both hav=
e more time?' Do not pursue them into the bedroom.</p></div></div></div></d=
