k border border-emerald-800/50">Firm</span></div><div><span class=3D"text-[=
10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold block mb-1">Why it works</span><=
p class=3D"text-emerald-200/80">This script names the rumination pattern wi=
thout involving your partner (which would make them the person responsible =
for stopping your anxiety). Writing it down honors the anxiety while creati=
ng a boundary against it consuming your evening. It also signals that you'r=
e building capacity to self-regulate.</p></div><div><span class=3D"text-[10=
px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold block mb-1">Expected Response</spa=
n><p class=3D"text-emerald-200/80">You will feel relief. Your nervous syste=
m will begin to trust that you can contain anxiety without needing immediat=
e external reassurance. Over time, this reduces the frequency of the panic-=
reassurance cycle.</p></div><div><span class=3D"text-[10px] uppercase text-=
emerald-500 font-bold block mb-1">If it fails</span><p class=3D"text-emeral=
d-200/80 border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/10 rounded p-2 text-red-200">I=
f you find yourself ruminating again 10 minutes later, the script isn't fai=
ling =E2=80=94 your nervous system is just depleted. This is a sign you nee=
d to add a physical activity (walk, stretching, cold water on your face) to=
 interrupt the loop, not a sign the script doesn't work.</p></div></div></d=
iv></div></div><div class=3D"bg-black/20 rounded-xl border border-emerald-9=
00/50 shadow-inner overflow-hidden"><button class=3D"w-full p-4 md:p-6 text=
-left flex items-center justify-between gap-4 md:cursor-default"><div class=
=3D"flex-1 min-w-0"><span class=3D"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wid=
er text-emerald-500 mb-1 block">Script 5</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-100=
 font-medium truncate md:whitespace-normal">You're about to rest or do some=
thing for yourself, and you feel guilty because your partner is relaxing an=
