/path></svg> The Script</span><p class=3D"text-lg md:text-xl font-medium te=
xt-white italic leading-relaxed">"I'm going to take an hour for myself righ=
t now. I'm not asking for permission, and I'm not going to feel guilty abou=
t this. I'll be back at [specific time]."</p></div><div class=3D"grid md:gr=
id-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm"><div><span class=3D"text-[10px] uppercase text-eme=
rald-500 font-bold block mb-1">Tone to Use</span><span class=3D"bg-emerald-=
950/50 text-emerald-300 px-2 py-1 rounded inline-block border border-emeral=
d-800/50">Firm</span></div><div><span class=3D"text-[10px] uppercase text-e=
merald-500 font-bold block mb-1">Why it works</span><p class=3D"text-emeral=
d-200/80">This script is deceptively simple: it names the action, removes t=
he request for permission (which puts your partner in the position of paren=
t/manager), and sets a boundary. It trains both of you that rest is not a p=
rivilege to be earned =E2=80=94 it's a necessity. This is essential to brea=
king the burnout cycle (87).</p></div><div><span class=3D"text-[10px] upper=
case text-emerald-500 font-bold block mb-1">Expected Response</span><p clas=
s=3D"text-emerald-200/80">Your partner may say nothing, or they may say 'Ok=
ay.' They may feel momentary guilt or defensiveness, but they will adapt. T=
he key is consistency: do this every time you rest, and the guilt will fade=
.</p></div><div><span class=3D"text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-=
bold block mb-1">If it fails</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-200/80 border b=
order-red-500/20 bg-red-500/10 rounded p-2 text-red-200">If your partner sa=
ys 'But I need you' or creates a problem while you're resting, return at yo=
ur stated time and say: 'I see you needed me. We can talk about this in 10 =
minutes. I'm keeping my boundary.' Do not skip your rest time. Your burnout=
 depends on this.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div c=
lass=3D"bg-white/5 rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8 border border-white/10 mt-8 hover=
:bg-white/10 transition-colors"><h3 class=3D"text-emerald-200 font-bold mb-=
6 flex items-center gap-2 text-xl"><svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg=
" width=3D"24" height=3D"24" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" fill=3D"none" stroke=3D"=
currentColor" stroke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=
=3D"round" class=3D"lucide lucide-clock text-emerald-400" aria-hidden=3D"tr=
ue"><path d=3D"M12 6v6l4 2"></path><circle cx=3D"12" cy=3D"12" r=3D"10"></c=
ircle></svg> 30-Day Recovery Calendar</h3><div class=3D"grid sm:grid-cols-2=
 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4"><div class=3D"bg-black/20 p-5 rounded-xl border bord=
er-emerald-900/50 shadow-inner flex flex-col h-full"><div class=3D"flex ite=
ms-center gap-2 mb-3 pb-3 border-b border-emerald-900/50"><span class=3D"bg=
-emerald-500 text-slate-950 font-black text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-sm upper=
case tracking-widest">Week 1</span></div><div class=3D"space-y-4 grow text-=
sm"><div><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-b=
old mb-1">Weekly Focus</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-100 font-medium">Inte=
rrupt the panic-reassurance cycle by learning to self-soothe when your part=
ner is silent</p></div><div><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase text=
-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1">Daily Action</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-20=
0/80">Every time you feel panic rising about your partner's silence or with=
drawal, pause and ask yourself: 'Is this about something they actually did,=
 or is this my nervous system looking for proof they still care?' Write dow=
n the answer. Do not reach out for reassurance. Instead, do one grounding a=
ctivity (5 minutes of deep breathing, a walk, or holding ice).</p></div><di=
v><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-=
1">What to Track</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-200/80">How many times per =
day you panic about silence. What triggers the panic (specific situations, =
times of day, topics). Whether your partner actually was pulling away or wh=
ether your anxiety created the distance. Notice if your partner seems less =
withdrawn when you don't pursue them.</p></div></div><div class=3D"mt-4 pt-=
4 border-t border-emerald-900/50"><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercas=
e text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1 flex items-center gap-1"><svg xmlns=3D"ht=
tp://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" =
fill=3D"none" stroke=3D"currentColor" stroke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"=
round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round" class=3D"lucide lucide-badge-check" aria-h=
idden=3D"true"><path d=3D"M3.85 8.62a4 4 0 0 1 4.78-4.77 4 4 0 0 1 6.74 0 4=
 4 0 0 1 4.78 4.78 4 4 0 0 1 0 6.74 4 4 0 0 1-4.77 4.78 4 4 0 0 1-6.75 0 4 =
4 0 0 1-4.78-4.77 4 4 0 0 1 0-6.76Z"></path><path d=3D"m9 12 2 2 4-4"></pat=
h></svg> Success Metric</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-300 font-medium text=
-sm">By end of week 1, you should have at least 3 instances where you felt =
panic, self-soothed, and your partner remained engaged (they didn't actuall=
y pull away). You should feel noticeably less exhausted from managing your =
own anxiety.</p></div></div><div class=3D"bg-black/20 p-5 rounded-xl border=
 border-emerald-900/50 shadow-inner flex flex-col h-full"><div class=3D"fle=
x items-center gap-2 mb-3 pb-3 border-b border-emerald-900/50"><span class=
=3D"bg-emerald-500 text-slate-950 font-black text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-sm=
 uppercase tracking-widest">Week 2</span></div><div class=3D"space-y-4 grow=
 text-sm"><div><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 =
font-bold mb-1">Weekly Focus</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-100 font-medium=
">Stop being the manager/parent and start being a partner by having ONE con=
versation about how you actually want to divide responsibilities</p></div><=
div><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold m=
b-1">Daily Action</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-200/80">Spend 10 minutes e=
ach day noticing where you're managing, controlling, or parenting your part=
ner. Write down 3-5 specific examples (reminding them about appointments, o=
rganizing their things, managing their emotions, etc.). By Thursday, choose=
 ONE thing you're going to stop doing. On Friday, have the conversation usi=
ng the script from Situation 2: 'I've been carrying a lot, and I've been do=
ing it quietly...'</p></div><div><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase=
 text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1">What to Track</span><p class=3D"text-emer=
ald-200/80">How much energy you free up when you stop managing one thing. W=
hether your partner rises to the occasion or whether the thing doesn't get =
done (and whether that's actually your problem). How your partner responds =
when you position this as a partnership redesign, not an accusation.</p></d=
iv></div><div class=3D"mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-emerald-900/50"><span clas=
s=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1 flex items=
-center gap-1"><svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width=3D"12" heigh=
t=3D"12" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" fill=3D"none" stroke=3D"currentColor" stroke=
-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round" class=3D"lu=
cide lucide-badge-check" aria-hidden=3D"true"><path d=3D"M3.85 8.62a4 4 0 0=
