<path d=3D"m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg> Success Metric</span><p class=3D"te=
xt-emerald-300 font-medium text-sm">You have the conversation by Friday. Yo=
ur partner agrees to take on at least one thing you've been managing. You f=
eel noticeably less resentful, even if the thing isn't done perfectly. You =
notice your partner treating you slightly differently =E2=80=94 with less d=
efensiveness, more collaboration.</p></div></div><div class=3D"bg-black/20 =
p-5 rounded-xl border border-emerald-900/50 shadow-inner flex flex-col h-fu=
ll"><div class=3D"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3 pb-3 border-b border-emerald=
-900/50"><span class=3D"bg-emerald-500 text-slate-950 font-black text-xs px=
-2 py-0.5 rounded-sm uppercase tracking-widest">Week 3</span></div><div cla=
ss=3D"space-y-4 grow text-sm"><div><span class=3D"block text-[10px] upperca=
se text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1">Weekly Focus</span><p class=3D"text-eme=
rald-100 font-medium">Rebuild emotional intimacy (not sexual intimacy yet) =
by having one unstructured conversation with your partner where you're genu=
inely curious about them</p></div><div><span class=3D"block text-[10px] upp=
ercase text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1">Daily Action</span><p class=3D"text=
-emerald-200/80">Each evening, ask your partner one question that is NOT ab=
out logistics, problems, or the relationship. Examples: 'What made you laug=
h today?' 'What's something you've been thinking about?' 'If you could do a=
nything this weekend, what would it be?' Listen to the answer without probl=
em-solving or redirecting to yourself. Do not use this conversation to lead=
 into sex. Just let it be connection.</p></div><div><span class=3D"block te=
xt-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1">What to Track</span><p=
 class=3D"text-emerald-200/80">Whether your partner opens up more when you'=
re not demanding reassurance. Whether you feel more connected to them as a =
person. Whether the 'roommate' feeling starts to shift. Notice your own urg=
e to turn the conversation into an opportunity to be heard =E2=80=94 resist=
 it this week.</p></div></div><div class=3D"mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-emera=
ld-900/50"><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font=
-bold mb-1 flex items-center gap-1"><svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/sv=
g" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" fill=3D"none" stroke=3D=
"currentColor" stroke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=
=3D"round" class=3D"lucide lucide-badge-check" aria-hidden=3D"true"><path d=
=3D"M3.85 8.62a4 4 0 0 1 4.78-4.77 4 4 0 0 1 6.74 0 4 4 0 0 1 4.78 4.78 4 4=
 0 0 1 0 6.74 4 4 0 0 1-4.77 4.78 4 4 0 0 1-6.75 0 4 4 0 0 1-4.78-4.77 4 4 =
0 0 1 0-6.76Z"></path><path d=3D"m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg> Success Metri=
c</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-300 font-medium text-sm">By end of week 3,=
 you've had 7 of these conversations. Your partner is sharing more. You fee=
l like you're remembering who they are as a person, not just as someone who=
 manages your anxiety. The intimacy score hasn't changed on paper, but it f=
eels different in the room.</p></div></div><div class=3D"bg-black/20 p-5 ro=
unded-xl border border-emerald-900/50 shadow-inner flex flex-col h-full"><d=
iv class=3D"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3 pb-3 border-b border-emerald-900/5=
0"><span class=3D"bg-emerald-500 text-slate-950 font-black text-xs px-2 py-=
0.5 rounded-sm uppercase tracking-widest">Week 4</span></div><div class=3D"=
space-y-4 grow text-sm"><div><span class=3D"block text-[10px] uppercase tex=
t-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1">Weekly Focus</span><p class=3D"text-emerald-1=
00 font-medium">Establish a new rhythm around physical affection and sex th=
at is based on connection, not management</p></div><div><span class=3D"bloc=
k text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1">Daily Action</span=
><p class=3D"text-emerald-200/80">Every single day, initiate one small phys=
ical touch that is NOT sexual and NOT transactional: hold their hand while =
watching TV, hug them when you see them, touch their arm when you're talkin=
g. Do NOT do this as a way to earn sex or manage their mood. Do it because =
you're rebuilding the physical safety between you. If your partner initiate=
s sex, use the script from Situation 3 if you're not feeling connected. If =
you ARE feeling connected after three weeks of emotional intimacy work, say=
 yes and notice the difference.</p></div><div><span class=3D"block text-[10=
px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1">What to Track</span><p class=
=3D"text-emerald-200/80">Whether your partner reciprocates the small touche=
s. Whether sex, when it happens, feels different (more present, less transa=
ctional). Whether the spark (40) shows any signs of life. Notice your guilt=
 about rest =E2=80=94 it should be significantly lower by now.</p></div></d=
iv><div class=3D"mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-emerald-900/50"><span class=3D"b=
lock text-[10px] uppercase text-emerald-500 font-bold mb-1 flex items-cente=
r gap-1"><svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width=3D"12" height=3D"1=
